   <description>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">During 2018 CCJ continue to represent 744 cases of land dispossession through 92 legal processes (legal claims before the agrarian judges) in Antioquia, Sucre, Bolivar, Magdalena, Cesar and Meta.&#xA0; ByDecember 2018, 290 of these 744 cases had positive ruling and 160 are in the tribunal ready for verdict. The 290 cases are developed through of 51 legal processes. The 744 cases include 3898 people of which 49% are women and claims over 10 203 hectares of land. 
On the other hand, CCJ has contributed to raising awareness and knowledge transfer about land restitution legal proceedings to public institutions, social organizations and academia through 7 specialized meetings and 2 publications.</narrative>
   </description>
